Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Dice @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with large drizzle of @olive oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}. Halve @lemon{1}. In a #small bowl{}, combine @apricot jam{2%tablespoon}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, half the @ancho chili powder{1%teaspoon}, and ¼ cup water (⅓ cup for 4 servings).

In a second small bowl, combine shallot, juice from lemon halves, @sugar{½%teaspoon}, and a pinch of salt. Set aside, stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

Pat @chicken breasts{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt and pepper. Heat a large drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #plate{}. Add jam mixture to pan and cook until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from heat; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

In a #large bowl{}, toss together @mixed greens{2%ounce}, pickled shallot (and pickling liquid), a large drizzle of @olive oil{}, and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Divide potatoes, chicken, and salad between plates. Top chicken with sauce and serve.